text: Saris - $35 each - I have only 1 of these left Yakima - $40 each - I have only 1 of these left Thule - no longer available  These allow step-thru ladies bike frames, or any bike with a low top tube, like a full suspension bike, or kids bike, to be mounted on a bike rack. The adapter gives the bike a horizontal top tube so that the bike hangs on the rack properly. Non-standard frames are a real pain to strap onto a rack, often ending up hanging crooked and not too secure.  These are very secure. Easy to get on and off. One end of it clips on the handlebar stem under the bars and the other end clips under the seat.  The adapter telescopes longer or shorter to fit the bike.  The adapter becomes the bike's top tube that gets strapped into the rack.  I don't believe bike shops have these currently because of the shortages.   Can meet in a public place. Firm price.    dog

title: Ladies Schwinn Hybrid full refurb Fits 5ft5 to 6ft
text: 2015 Schwinn Clear Creek hybrid road bike in very pretty condition.  The bike was completely disassembled, deep cleaned, and rebuilt, piece by piece. It has new stainless steel cables, new cable housings, and new internal ball bearings. Everything works perfectly. And it rides nice and smooth.... Better than new, as mass assembled bikes don't get a mechanic's touch during build-out, often needing grease around the bearings and adjustments to most components. This one also had cheap galvanized cables on it that would rust. Those have all been replaced.  The bike has a 15 inch frame measured from the bottom bracket to the top of the seat tube. I would call this a medium size bike. A rider around 5ft5 to around 6'0 should fit fine.  The bike was completely disassembled. All the components and the drivetrain were removed, deep-cleaned, and adjusted. The front shock was removed and the headset bearings were replaced, greased, and the headset was adjusted. The wheelhub bearings were all replaced, greased, and adjusted. The internal cups and cones where all these bearings travel were all deep-cleaned to provide the cleanest and smoothest surface possible. The wheelhubs are now buttery smooth. The bottom bracket was rebuilt with new ball bearings and fresh grease, and tightened correctly. The wheels were trued, the rims and spokes were individually cleaned. The frame was cleaned and polished. The brake calipers and levers, shifters, derailleurs, cranks and chainrings, and drivetrain were all disassembled and rebuilt. There's not a nut or bolt on the bike I haven't touched.  This is a 21-speed comfort road bike with a step thru frame. The bike has street tires(700c). It has a front shock. The bike has Shimano Tourney derailleurs. It has a Shimano grip shifters. The bike has a shock absorbing seat post and matching seat and grips. The wheels have lightweight alloy rims and hubs, and have nice tires with excellent tread. The bike also has an alloy stem, alloy handlebar, and alloy seatpost to keep things light-ish. The frame is very pretty and is in like new condition.  Due to the vast amount of spam, please put the word DOG into your email and I will reply.   Use the "more ads by this user" link to see my other bikes. Link is located on the right side of the ad.    Old grease, combined with dirt, will harden and damage the operation of the bearings. This will cause internal damage, and can make your bike dangerous(especially with the headset bearings which allow you to steer). If you're looking to buy any used bike, find out when the last time the bearings were overhauled (not just a "tune-up"). If it has not been done in 5 yrs, I strongly recommend having it done.

title: 2008 Specialized Ruby Pro 52 cm Women's Full Carbon Road Bike Dura Ace
text: This is a 2008 Specialized Ruby Pro is very close to new condition.  The only obvious wear is a rub mark on the right crank arm (see pic) and some scratches on the shifter plates (see pics).  It even has the original sticker set on it.  Absolutely nice enough to give as a gift.  Just over 16 pounds on my digital bike scale.  This one has a beautiful Gloss Red Tint with Silver paint job.  It was originally $4400 plus tax in 2008, but since bikes are now so insanely expensive, the new ones are now an eye-watering $8700 plus tax, but they are sold out anyway.  Works great.  2 x 10 Dura Ace drivetrain with a carbon S-Works crankset and Ultegra brakes.  The saddle is fine, but it really is just a filler.  We are keeping the saddle we were using.

I have not seen another one on the trail.

title: 2018 Giant FastRoad SLR 1
text: 2018 Giant FastRoad SLR 1. Size is Medium/Large (M/L). I'm 5'9-5"10" and the bike is a perfect fit, nicely stretched out for road riding. Light, fast, very smooth ride. Shimano (Tiagra) road bike components...very solid equipment group. I bought this model specifically because of the Shimano hydraulic disc brakes which are very powerful and super smooth. Every other manufacturer that year seemed to be downgrading brakes to Tektro to save money. The bike has literally 100-200 road miles on it. I was/am working through a back injury that kept me from riding much shortly after I got it, and I don't ride at all now. So, when I say "like new", it's not B.S.   Here is a link to Giant's archived Web page: https://www.giant-bicycles.com/us/bikes-fastroad-slr-2018  The Fastroad SLR 1 was made of ultralight aluminum tubing and has a carbon fork.   I generally hate Craigslist because of the crazies, so be forewarned I'm not going to play games with anyone. No trades, crazy schemes, payment plans, etc. You will get the bike in exactly the condition I'm describing along with all the original paperwork, purchase invoice, etc. Looking for a straightforward sale from a buyer with cash. Test rides with cash held by me from a public location near a police station. Like I said, no games.

title: 2022 Specialized Stumpjumper Comp 29" XXL S6
text: Bike is essentially new. I bought it after getting out of the hospital from a catastrophic injury with the hopes of getting back into riding again, but more problems have popped up since and I will unlikely ever ride bikes again in any meaningful way. Bike was bought brand new from Epic, and ridden 3 times for a total of 80 miles. Day one upgrades were Whisky 35x760 carbon handlebars, ODI dreadlock grips, Raceface 40mm stem, Vittoria Barzo 2.35 race compound tires, muc-off valves and tubeless set up, and a DT Swiss 1900 rear wheel with a 370 hub. As expected, bike is essentially spotless. Its a big bike, 6'5" ish and above. Im 6'8" for reference. My favorite part of this bike is the 35mm seatpost. Larger riders like myself have a tendency to wear out standard sized dropper posts when they are extended out of the frame enough to fit the bike, and the newer 35mm stuff is significantly stronger thn prior sizes such as 30.9mm. Bike has SX drivetrain, X fusion 130mm shock, Tektro Gemini brakes with 180mm rotors and Rockshox 140mm recon fork as it is the base model of the stumpjumper. Boost spacing and thru-axles. Bike is also for sale at Great Bicycle shop where it can be seen and test ridden. It can be bought outside of the shop if preferred   NO TRADES

title: Salsa Campeon Road Bike 65cm XXL Tiagra Dura-Ace
text: Built this up from a used frame I found a while back. Bontrager Racelite wheels with titanium axles, Michelin Power Pure tires (lighter and less rolling resistance than a GP5000, but a little thinner A very sporty tire at about 50% wear). Full brand new Tiagra 2x10 groupset with 0 miles, brand new Shimano BB, Dura Ace calipers from I believe 3 series ago, so they are old but with brand new pads and are immaculate as is. I originally built the bike up with a full Dura Ace group that matched the calipers but the derailleurs were shot, so I just threw a complete Tiagra group on it. This new 10 speed tiagra shifts wonderfully, nothing like last gen 9 speed stuff. Easton 70 series carbon seatpost with polished head, Bontrager Racelite titanium saddle with red rails. Bontrager Elite stem (i think), and XXX Bontrager carbon bars in 44cm. This is a big bike, for riders 6'5" and above, but is no slouch Scandium aluminum frame with carbon fork from back when Salsa made road bikes in the early 2000s. As it sits, it has zero miles, I built it up before getting horrifically injured, and I will not be able to ride bikes again unfortunately, so Im thinning out the garage. I never even got to enjoy this one. 50/36 chainrings, 11-28 cassette . Good all around gearing. Derailleur can handle up to a 32 i believe, if you find yourself climbing all day. Bike is also for sale at Great Bicycle Shop where it can be seen and test ridden. Can be bought outside of the shop though, if you prefer. Very unique frame, Ive never seen another like it, and it in great shape save for some very minor wear. It is 20 years old, so its amazing the paint still pops like it does. I matched everything up to suit the early 2000s theme from the wheels to the bars to the saddle and seat post. Clearance for 25s only, maybe 26s. I was able to cram a 28 on the front bit the back was a no-go. Not accepting trades right now, I have to move soon and don't need to take a lot with me.  NO TRADES

title: 1974 Honda CB360T, extra parts
text: Well-kept antique, vintage Honda motorcycle. This bike was stored for a few years and has been revived. Just under 9700K original miles. The dent-free, primered tank has been red-coated on the inside, carbs have been rebuilt, new plugs, fresh oil, pod air filters, custom battery box, fuel lines, fuel filters, and a new gas cap seal have all been added. It starts and runs and pulls in all gears but hasn't been ridden yet this year. It will need a new battery. The tires are not dry rotted, it's been stored indoors all the years I've owned it. It's almost 50 years old. If you are into vintage bikes at all you are aware that they always need a little something tweaked or some basic maintenance or check-up. Pre-ride checks are super important.    This machine has a very cool vintage bike patina going on. Cool but not perfect in any way, worn in but serviceable. It's a real head-turner. The CB360T came stock with a 6-speed transmission which gave it a higher top-end speed versus the CB350, not that it was any better bike. The motor is strong, this bike just needs a good check up by a qualified tech and it'll be ready for the road. I'll send you a detailed list of the extra parts included if you reply with legit contact information. This bike has a clean TN title. I don't need help selling this, if you see this ad then it is still available and still for sale-don't ask, I won't reply to suspicious anything, I won't ship it, no scams. Thanks.

title: 2008 Specialized Ruby Pro 52 cm Women's Full Carbon Road Bike Dura Ace
text: This is a 2008 Specialized Ruby Pro is very close to new condition.  The only obvious wear is a rub mark on the right crank arm (see pic) and some scratches on the shifter plates (see pics).  It even has the original sticker set on it.  Absolutely nice enough to give as a gift.  Just over 16 pounds on my digital bike scale.  This one has a beautiful Gloss Red Tint with Silver paint job.  It was originally $4400 plus tax in 2008, but since bikes are now so insanely expensive, the new ones are now an eye-watering $8700 plus tax, but they are sold out anyway.  Works great.  2 x 10 Dura Ace drivetrain with a carbon S-Works crankset and Ultegra brakes.  The saddle is fine, but it really is just a filler.  We are keeping the saddle we were using.

title: Paramount Series 50 mountain bike, adult small/medium commuter, hybrid
text: Schwinn Paramount Series 50 from 1991.   This is not your department store Schwinn, but rather a somewhat collectible steel mountain bike, and one of the last bikes to be welded in Japan from Schwinn/Paramount as they entered the high-end mountain bike scene in the early 1990s.  16" frame, so Adult small, good for folks maybe 5-0 to 5-8. My first mountain bike back in early 90s, saved for my kids, now they have outgrown.  26" wheels, original Shimano DX 3x7 group, replaced knobbies with smooth tread Continental tires for greenway/gravel. Newer flat pedals and grips and saddle.  Bag and rack to be used on another bike, but if I haven't swapped that over yet, we can negotiate including those.

title: Top Tube Adapter for Women's Bikes and Full Suspension Bikes
text: Saris - $35 each - I have only 1 of these left Yakima - $40 each - I have only 1 of these left Thule - no longer available  These allow step-thru ladies bike frames, or any bike with a low top tube, like a full suspension bike, or kids bike, to be mounted on a bike rack. The adapter gives the bike a horizontal top tube so that the bike hangs on the rack properly. Non-standard frames are a real pain to strap onto a rack, often ending up hanging crooked and not too secure.  These are very secure. Easy to get on and off. One end of it clips on the handlebar stem under the bars and the other end clips under the seat.  The adapter telescopes longer or shorter to fit the bike.  The adapter becomes the bike's top tube that gets strapped into the rack.  I don't believe bike shops have these currently because of the shortages.   Can meet in a public place. Firm price.    dog

title: Yakima 4 Bike Tilt Out Hitch Rack with Integrated Locking System
text: This listing is for a Yakima 4 Bike Tilt Out Hitch Rack with Integrated Locking System. Rack natively fits 1 1/4" receivers. This listing also includes a CURT 45770 Trailer Hitch Receiver Adapter Reducer, 2" to 1 1/4" allowing the rack to work with both receiver sizes. There are two hitch locks one for the rack and one for the adapter. The rack itself has a cable lock made into one of the bike support arms that pulls out of one of the tubes to secure bikes to the rack. All straps and keys are present. I have used this rack behind a Honda Accord and an F150 and it works great on both vehicles.   I am located on the north side of Cullman, AL (i65 Exit 310). I am also in Huntsville weekly and happy to setup a time and place to meet in the Madison / Huntsville area.  Text: EightFive9-FiveSeven6dashNineTooOneEight

title: LA Wheel Chock
text: Fully adjustable motorcycle chock for any tire. LA Chock Fully Adjustable for any size tire Fully adjustable, fits tires from 80mm to 190mm and 15‚Ä≥ to 26‚Ä≥ wheels Rugged, beautiful powdercoat Integral brackets for bolting down to a trailer Made in the USA The LA Chock (and the smaller footprint LA Trailer Chock) is an innovative and secure motorcycle chock that can be adjusted to fit any size motorcycle tire. Use the LA Chock on your garage floor to provide secure, upright storage for your motorcycle. Just place the stand on the floor and push or ride the motorcycle into the stand. The patented stand clamps onto the front tire and securely holds the motorcycle upright. You can now get off the bike and perform cleaning or maintenance tasks. Mount the LA Chock or the LA Trailer Chock in a trailer and your towing worries are over. Loading is as easy as riding the bike into the stand. Once in, you can get off the bike and secure the bike with straps without someone else having to hold the bike up for you. Another great benefit of using the LA Chock is that no front tie downs are necessary. Just secure the rear of the motorcycle with straps and the chock does the rest.  Like new condition.  Will hold large bikes. Have 2 of these available $150 each or both for $275 or trade for something cool.   Can meet in local Huntsville,AL area   Will not ship or tolerate any other scams   Thanks

title: Azonic outlaw 26‚Äù wheel set
text: Barely used wheel set, has a few scratches, no dents $175 obo Azonic Outlaw 26" Wheelset If you're a hard-charging rider that doesn't sweat a few grams if it means your wheels hold up to abuse, these wheels are for you! Azonic Outlaws have been one of our favorite and best selling wheelsets over the years here at Jenson USA. Why? They can take just about any abuse you can throw their way, at a price you can't beat. With solid, convertible sealed-bearing hubs paired to burly alloy rims with stainless spokes, these wheels area ready to carry you through the chunk without taking a chunk out of your wallet. Depending on the rear wheel spacing of your frame, choose between the 135mm and 150mm option. 135mm will be compatible with most modern trail bikes, especially with a 142x12mm axle conversion (Sold Separately). 150mm will work many burly downhill bikes. For both the 135mm and 150mm options, the front wheel is compatible with quick release and 20mm forks. Adapters included in the box. 15mmx100mm front axle conversion caps sold separately: HU269Z00 12x142mm rear axle kit sold separately: HU254Z02 (Compatible only with 135mm option) 6 bolt disc rotor compatible 25mm inner rim width offers plenty of support for todays larger casing tire. Freehub is compatible with Shimano 8/9/10/11 speed cassettes, and SRAM 8/9/10 speed cassettes 32 spoke count front and rear Tubeless Compatible Approx Weight: 135mm 2340g, 150mm 2362g

title: 57 cm. Trek Earl Fixie
text: For those who attempted to contact me, please try again.  I had a medical emergency and could not answer the phone.   One hundred and thirty-six years later, the appeal of the fixed-gear bicycle is simplicity, not safety.  There‚Äôs very little to go wrong. These bikes are heavy-duty, weather-resistant, long-lived, and charming in their lack of levers and mechanical addenda. Mandatory in the secretive world of professional bike messengers.  Less than one mile ridden.  Chromoly steel frame by TREK.  Perfect for the streets of the Big Easy.  New rims, tires, tubes, chain, crank, peddles, and Trek Earl (https://uncrate.com/trek-earl-bike/) frame.  You can have your choice of seat.  The rear rim is flip-flop offering freewheel and fixed drive modes as standard.  The rear caliper brakes by Tektro provide all the stopping power necessary.  This is a MUST sell to the best offer.

title: 2018 Giant FastRoad SLR 1
text: 2018 Giant FastRoad SLR 1. Size is Medium/Large (M/L). I'm 5'9-5"10" and the bike is a perfect fit, nicely stretched out for road riding. Light, fast, very smooth ride. Shimano (Tiagra) road bike components...very solid equipment group. I bought this model specifically because of the Shimano hydraulic disc brakes which are very powerful and super smooth. Every other manufacturer that year seemed to be downgrading brakes to Tektro to save money. The bike has literally 100-200 road miles on it. I was/am working through a back injury that kept me from riding much shortly after I got it, and I don't ride at all now. So, when I say "like new", it's not B.S.   Here is a link to Giant's archived Web page: https://www.giant-bicycles.com/us/bikes-fastroad-slr-2018  The Fastroad SLR 1 was made of ultralight aluminum tubing and has a carbon fork.   I generally hate Craigslist because of the crazies, so be forewarned I'm not going to play games with anyone. No trades, crazy schemes, payment plans, etc. You will get the bike in exactly the condition I'm describing along with all the original paperwork, purchase invoice, etc. Looking for a straightforward sale from a buyer with cash. Test rides with cash held by me from a public location near a police station. Like I said, no games.

weldmaster, cooper Accord Samsung 7 Drilling transmission, Combo  Industrial Thrift Store Shipping Available  Below is a bit of about our mission/concept of repurposing.  First off, what are some examples of repurposing? It is taking a byproduct or waste stream such as a retired street sweeper brush and giving it a 2nd life as a back scratcher for horses or cattle. It is taking a decommissioned fire hose and giving it an extended life as a boat dock fender. It is taking an obsolete ski lift cable and giving it a second life as hand railing in a luxury condo building.   In your efforts to reach Zero Waste, do you have any byproducts or waste from projects now, or coming up, that would be a candidate for repurposing? Or, do you have any surplus/obsolete inventories or idle equipment you'd like to deal on. . . maybe items that have been depreciated out, over orders on a job, inventory from a project that got cancelled, etc.?  We look forward to being a resource on any byproducts, waste, inventories, or equipment that would be a candidate for repurposing!   To date, our company has helped a number of organizations through repurposing: US Army, Denver Broncos, City of Chicago, Nestles, BNSF Railroad, Oklahoma State University, Purina, US National Forest Service, Campbells Soup, State of Wyoming, Paramount Pictures, and many, many more! _________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________  We are America's largest Industrial Thrift Store! text: This listing is for a Yakima 4 Bike Tilt Out Hitch Rack with Integrated Locking System. Rack natively fits 1 1/4" receivers. This listing also includes a CURT 45770 Trailer Hitch Receiver Adapter Reducer, 2" to 1 1/4" allowing the rack to work with both receiver sizes. There are two hitch locks one for the rack and one for the adapter. The rack itself has a cable lock made into one of the bike support arms that pulls out of one of the tubes to secure bikes to the rack. All straps and keys are present. I have used this rack behind a Honda Accord and an F150 and it works great on both vehicles.   I am located on the north side of Cullman, AL (i65 Exit 310). text: This is a 700c road bike from Kent that is made for all sorts of different terrain options. People call these bikes many things from a Gravel Grinder to an Adventure Road Bike to an Urban Adventure Bike or whatever you would like to call this versatile bike. The Kent Nazz will answer the call for many riding surfaces and styles. The Steel frame and fork with 700C x 40 textured tires will keep you riding solid and smooth on gravel or paved pathways or pothole filled urban roads. The front and rear cable actuated disc brakes provide powerful braking when things get fast and keep you in full control regardless of the road surface. Adventure Bike inspired 2X drivetrain has Shimano shifters and a Shimano rear derailleur to give you all the gearing you need to tackle any terrain you may encounter on your cycling adventure. The Kent Nazz will be the bike that easily fill all of your biking needs. title: Schwinn varsity
text: Description  Here is an original February 1979 VINTAGE  (The mens SCHWINN VARSITY 10-speed road bike with 27" wheels. It is in the original and very appealing CAMPUS GREEN factory paint. If you like unique unrestored original bikes with BETTER FEATURES, this may be a great bike for you. With the insanely high price of gas (and the economy being bad) now is the time to ride a cool vintage bike!  *This bike has a cool mens original road bike frame and forks with original paint and decals, with a little wear cool and comfortable riding street bike style handlebars, wrapped hand grips, Schwinn neck, twin stick shifters, Schwinn derailleur, Center Pull brakes, Schwinn cruiser bike seat/saddle, bear claw pedals, and more!  This bike has the convenience of 10-speeds!  *Remember the Schwinn Continental and Varsity road bikes? EVERYONE wanted one back in the day! Now you almost never see them! Bring back some fond memories and create some great new ones as well!  *The tires are 27x1 1/4". They are new and hold air *The bike is an original TEN SPEED and the gears do operate may need adjustment. The hand controlled brakes are operable as well. (May need adjustment)  *DIMENSIONS  A good height for a slightly taller rider that would enjoy a vintage Chicago Schwinn bicycle! The standover height is approx 33 1/4". The distance from the floor to the top of the seat post clamp is approx 34". The distance from the center of the crank to the top of the seat post clamp is approx 24". The center of the handlebar stem to the center of the seat post is approx 22". The bike will accomadate most any rider comfortably. The seat height is easy to adjust.

title: 1968 Honda SCRAMBLER 90
text: Very Rare CL-90 Scrambler in Candy Red. Second year for HONDA's first Off-Road(vs. trail bikes) capable 90cc Motorcycle, based on the famous SUPER 90 street bike, with the 8hp engine! This bike, like it's street cousin, can do an honest 65mph in 4th gear! Still has the original 8hp Carburetor with it's correct intake manifold and air-cleaner boot. Sadly, it's missing the original engine and exhaust, as well as the air-cleaner and seat. Tank also needs new badges and knee-pads. Fortunately, all of these missing parts(including engine) are commonly available new or used on ebay, and all are still made to this day, for sale in the Asian markets(search for Super 90 and CM-200 parts)! Everything there is all original, right down to the tires and grips. The chromed fenders are both straight, but starting to get tarnished. It has the rear passenger foot-pegs too. In storage for almost 20 years. I was going to restore it(they sell for over $2,400), but I'll never have time to finish it. Good rolling project bike. I'll help you load. Asking $1,200 or best offer. Trade considered, but only if you include pictures.

title: KONA STINKY DEE-LUXE
text: Serious downhill Mullet 69er. This is an older and rare build which I intended to complete as an e-bike with a mid-mount Bafang kit but think it is going to be too much for me to handle (I just turned 70 and will go for something a little more sensible). So for 12 to 15 hundred bucks more you could have really fast and stable e-ride at reasonable cost; or leave as is for a unique,tough downhill ride. Approx 19 inch frame with 33inch standover height and amazing 15inch clearance which gives plenty of clearance for a motor. Plenty of triangle space for a battery.DNM double crown inverted fork (which was over $500 alone) and has 20mm thru axle. 29 x 2.6 inch front Easton tubeless wheel (over $300) with new Kenda Hellkat Pro tire. Rear wheel is Mavic D521 q/r with new Kenda Nevegal pro tubed tire. 1x9 setup with oval 36T narrow/wide chainring and Shimano XTR  with new Sunrace 11/32 casette,new Shimano ebike chain. Fox Vanilla R shock. New KS mechanical dropper post. New Answer 810mm flat bar with ergo grips. Beefy Truativ stem and gripshift shifter. Hayes hydraulic brakes with 205mm front and 160 rear discs. Have other bars/shifters/saddles as options Definitely built for the taller rider. Cash only.

title: Surly Steamroller - 53cm
text: Up for sale is a fixed gear Surly Steamroller.  It has a flip/flop hub, but only the fixed side is set up. It would be super easy to convert to a singlespeed (slap a freewheel on the other side of the hub, flip the wheel around, and coast to your heart's content).   I put brand new Panaracer GravelKing tires on the bike in the fall, still have tons of life left. At 38mm wide, they're provide a smooth ride on all of the gravel bike paths we have around town!  This bike looks beautiful (it's gotten compliments from total strangers multiple times), and is a blast to ride. Unfortunately it's a little too small for me, which discourages me from taking it on longer rides. So it's time to find it a new home! Make me an offer!

title: 1979 Wet Bike
text: READ everything below. If you see the post, then I have the machine. I delete my posts once sold. Firm on this price. Transferable AZ registration in hand. NO TRADES (other than older off road MX bikes that would be delivered). Contact NineSevenZero, TwoZeroEight, FiveZeroFiveTwo because no one seems to be getting my craigs email replies.  1979 WetBike. Made from 78 to I think 92. This is the Suzuki 723cc 50hp model. Plenty of vid's on Youtube. Everything works on this machine. I removed and cleaned the carbs. Bilge pump works. Exhaust fan works. No cracks in the ski's. No cracks in the body. Aluminum impeller is in great shape. Very clean inside engine compartment. May need a bit of "tuning" again. Was last used back in 1997. Previous owner died but his grandson told me that it was a low hour machine that was only used on the Patagonia Lake back before they closed down the personal watercraft usage on that water. Afterwards, this Wetbike sat in the back yard for the rest of its life.  Cosmetically it needs a few things. I have found a few sources for nearly almost every part you would need to get this classic looking good again and will turn the buyer onto these sources to save you time. Decals, grips, seat foam & cover. Dolly has new tires as of last month. This could be ready to go in short order. I have come to realize that I am not going to drive 3-4 hours (or more) to put this in water and enjoy it especially with these Biden fuel prices. Just not gonna happen. Buyers in Phoenix or Lake Havasu area can more enjoy this machine.  Located in Saint David, AZ. If you don't know where that is...Google it. title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System for Motorcycles/bikes
text: Like new condition, had it less than a month. Just purchased a new bike that has a TPMS from the factory, so I no longer need this one.   Just download the FOBO app, sync it up, and you're ready to ride!   FOBO Bike 2 Tire Pressure Monitoring Systems  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) for every biker. FOBO Bike 2 uses the latest Bluetooth 5.0 technology that works directly with your smartphone that has Bluetooth smart Ready (Bluetooth 4.0 or above) capability in order to use FOBO Bike 2. Currently FOBO Bike 2 works best with iOS 9.3 and Android 5.0 or later.  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system for every biker  * View on demand tire pressure & temperature  * Monitors tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range  * Detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies  * Sends instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/smartwatch/Bluetooth headset  * Easy install on any motorcycle without running wires, drilling holes, and tedious programming   The main function of FOBO Bike 2 is to monitor tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range. It detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies. It then transmits the readings to a smart phone where the user can browse. The user can set upper and lower thresholds of the air pressure. FOBO Bike 2 can send instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/ smartwatch/ Bluetooth headset. title: Turner Czar XT Carbon XL Low Miles
text: This brand new $5,995 Turner Czar Carbon XT was listed in Pinkbike classifieds back in July 2018. It was for sale in Delaware for $3,750.  I had them convert the chainring to a Wolf Tooth 30T and had it shipped (see photos for the original receipt).  I had Andrew at Bikesmith do the assembly when it arrived.  The following components are on the bike: *  Carbon frame *  Fox Float 32 CTD Fit 100mm w/Kashima Fork *  Fox Float CTD w/ Kashima rear shock *  Shimano XT Gruppo  *  Thomson/Renthal cockpit  *  DT Swiss 350/Stan's ZTR Crest Alloy Wheelset  *  Renthal Fatbar Lite Carbon 40mm rise 740mm width 31.8 handlebar  *  Wolf Tooth 30T Drop-stop Chainring  *  Brand-X Ascend 125mm Dropper seatpost (The Ascend is almost exactly the same as the PNW‚Äôs                  Bachelor seat post and likely manufactured by PNW.) *  Wolf Tooth Dropper remote   *  Older Spank Oozy platform pedals as shown in photos (these can be included if you need them or removed)   *  SQ Labs 711 ergo grips OR the still new ODI Ruffian grips that came with the bike   *  ISM Adamo Peak OR the WTB Rocket Saddle that came with the bike  The specifications are reflected in the second photo under the XL size.  I have ridden this bike 1,478 miles over 121 rides since 2018 Rides: 21/2018, 33/2019, 57/2020, 10/2021.   I also own a Lynskey hardtail which get the majority of my saddle time.  Since 2018 the Lynskey has been ridden 3,354 miles or 70% of my total miles. If you weigh more than 190 the Stan's Crest wheelset is likely to take this bike out of your consideration.  The bike as shown weighs about 26.5 to 27.2 lbs without pedals using a less than precise bathroom scale although some reviews indicate a lower weight.  The last two photos show my receipt and the bike as it was originally equipped prior to the 1x10 conversion and the addition of components like the dropper post, handlebars, grips, saddle...  I also debadged the Stan's Crest Wheelset as the decals resulted in a cluttered look (Compare the second to last photo with the first photo to compare the before and after).    You can read some reviews on the Turner Czar on these websites: Singletracks, Bike Rumor, MB Action, MTBR and the Radavist. Price is firm given the low miles and condition of the bike and components. NO TRADES.    If you are interested in this bike please call me before 8pm to take a look and a spin.

title: Specialized Stumpjumper S-Works Carbon Bike
text: Selling my hardtail S-Works with absolute top-of-the-range components at the time, and very light (probably around 22 lbs). I bought it in Italy in 2012 and used it for a couple of years. When we moved to NYC in 2014, we left the bike unused until 2020, when we decided to move from NYC to Prescott. We brought it here, I changed the tires 6 months ago, and started to ride, but very rarely, and it is a pity to leave that beauty unused. Uphill is unbeatable, while downhill, does require skills, like any high-end hardtail.  Known problems: 1. The fork has been left unused for a long time, and it does require service. It works, but it is a bit stiff, and the rebound control is hard to command. Also, one of the stanchions is slightly damaged, due to the dirt that was retained by the seal (see photo). 2. Magura rotors are probably at 50% of their life 3. Some minor scratches on the pedals and the crankset from normal use  - Bike size M (17.5") - Year: 2012 - Hardtail - Fork: RockShox SID Brain BlackBox with 80 mm travel - Frame: FACT 11m carbon - Drivetrain: Sram XX 2*10  - Shifters: SRAM XX, 10-speed, carbon trigger, w/ MatchMaker clamps - Front Derailleur: SRAM XX, S3 direct mount for DMD, top-swing, top-pull - Rear Derailleur: SRAM XX, 10-speed, mid cage - Brakes: Magura MT (carbon) - Tires: Specialized Ground Control T5 29*2.35 (tubeless) - Pedals: Shimano XTR - Saddle: Fizik Antares - Rims: ZTR Crest 29er - Hubs: DT Swiss

title: WOLFE E Tricycle
text: Welcome to your new favourite way of getting around. With 3 wheels to ensure maximum stability and predictable handling, but without compromising on power and efficiency and a low step through frame for easy mounting and dismounting, Tucana says goodbye to the days of having to load up your car to go to the beach, or shop for groceries. Large baskets keep your cargo secure, a front drive motor pulls the trike evenly, and fat 4‚Äù wide tires and a suspension fork provide extra comfort and stability. Tucana also comes with a powerful 48V 500W Bafang front drive motor, has 5 levels of assistance, and Cadence 12 magnet PAS system to ensure a seamless and natural ride. Tucana is a workhorse! This is a beautiful well build trike even the Bike store owner was impressed with how strong this trike is built. We purchased it back in November 2021 and received it in February. We have changed our plans so we are selling it for the original  price. No waiting . Ready to ride today. Price includes a GIRO helmet, GIANT Lock and cable. The trike has pedal assist along with a throttle for no pedaling. About 50 mile range depending on assist level. There are 5 assist levels and a no assist option. Three disk brakes.

Just download the FOBO app, sync it up, and you're ready to ride!   FOBO Bike 2 Tire Pressure Monitoring Systems  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) for every biker. FOBO Bike 2 uses the latest Bluetooth 5.0 technology that works directly with your smartphone that has Bluetooth smart Ready (Bluetooth 4.0 or above) capability in order to use FOBO Bike 2. Currently FOBO Bike 2 works best with iOS 9.3 and Android 5.0 or later.  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system for every biker  * View on demand tire pressure & temperature  * Monitors tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range  * Detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies  * Sends instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/smartwatch/Bluetooth headset  * Easy install on any motorcycle without running wires, drilling holes, and tedious programming   The main function of FOBO Bike 2 is to monitor tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range. It detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies. It then transmits the readings to a smart phone where the user can browse. The user can set upper and lower thresholds of the air pressure. FOBO Bike 2 can send instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/ smartwatch/ Bluetooth headset. It will monitor the pressure based on the thresholds with its smart algorithm and will provide three levels of alerts when the thresholds are breached

title: CrossCurrent S e-bike medium frame=16.5‚Äù
text: Juiced Bikes brand, CrossCurrent S model The medium size frame (16.5‚Äù) it should fit people between the heights of 5‚Äô4‚Äù & 6‚Äô  This electric bike will get you where you want to go in a hurry, or if you want to peddle more you can cover some incredible distances. I would love to continue to ride it, however a disability is making it more dangerous for me. I need to get a tricycle.  :-)  If the Juiced Bikes brand made an electric tricycle, I would buy one in a heartbeat.  This particular model is no longer being manufactured. It has been replaced with the CrossCurrent X. This bike had an upgrade of a 17.4 amp hour battery, and a frame "brushed aluminum" finish, whereby the frames with the highest quality welds and craftsmanship were selected, since the metal was given a clear finish.    I have primarily used the electric assist with a torque sensor, rather than cadence. This makes my peddling feel rather natural. It has different levels of electrical assist. The lowest level (Eco) is designed to just overcome the extra weight of the bike.  Levels 1, 2 & 3 provide increasing assist up to 28 mph. Level S which stands for ‚ÄúSport‚Äù continues to provide assist without any upper speed limit.  The weight of the bike is significant. Maybe about 54 pounds or a little more since I have the extended range battery.  You must take that into account when braking. Remember physics ‚Ä¶ momentum includes velocity and MASS.  The bike is designed to support the extra weight with extra heavy duty spokes, frame, and hydraulic brakes.  I like the idea that the battery pack is on the front down tube and not on the back wheel. This means that one can haul some loads with the bike rack ‚Äî rated for 50 pounds.  The total payload limit is 350 pounds.  I believe you will find the bike is very well thought out and designed and the craftsmanship is excellent. Customer support is pretty good as well.  There was a little bit of assembly required when I received the bike. The headlamp/light they sent had some glue in one of the receptacles. The company quickly sent me a replacement.  I also had a time or two when a fault signal appeared on the charging unit. Technical support readily resolved the issue by walking me through some simple steps.   I have an electronic copy of the instruction manual.  There are a few scratches on it when is the bike tipped over. All damage seems to be cosmetic. I had a slow leak in the rear tire and had a local bike shop replace the tube. It was a bit of a challenge for them to get the wheel off, but they managed.

title: Giant Roam Mid-Drive 750W/20AH eBike
text: 2018 Giant Roam 2 Disc 750W Bafang Mid-Drive, 20AH battery ebike   For sale is my 2018 Giant Roam Mid-Drive conversion ebike. I built this in the fall of 2018 and used it primarily as a desert trails runner in the Tucson Arizona area over the winter of 2020-21. It likely has about 50 miles use at the most, as my rides were almost always 2 hour 6-8 mile runs in moderate desert trails and ATV roads. This bike allowed me to get back into cycling, which I love but don‚Äôt have the endurance to take on without help. I‚Äôve learned I can go anywhere and ride all I want, using all my own power that I‚Äôm able, but always having assistance when needed. It has ‚Äòset me free‚Äô and I love it. This bike works great as both a road bike and cross country trails. It is a size small, but as a 5‚Äô8‚Äù / 30‚Äù inseam individual, it‚Äôs not all that small. I found it just barely small enough. This 2018 model is more agile than the newer, more ‚Äòslack‚Äô 2021 frame (specs are available on the internet). This frame has a steeper head angle and shorter wheel base than the newer model. I attached a full details spec sheet as two of the images.  This bike is in excellent condition ‚Äì perfectly true wheels, no dents or dings anywhere, always either covered or garaged, and everything works great. I‚Äôm 70, so I don‚Äôt ride fast nor abuse my equipment, and I‚Äôm a retired auto tech, so I keep my toys in tip-top shape. There is minor paint damage from strapping the bike down for transport and a few minor scratches; but as you can see from the pictures, it still looks great. The tires are almost new; the tubes have Slime installed. The derailleur, cassette and chain are brand new, upgrading to a Shimano Deore derailleur and from the OE 36-11 to a 42-11 cassette for better low-gear performance in steeper, rockier terrain here in the Huachuca mountains of Sierra Vista. The 20AH Lithium battery pack is brand new (I‚Äôm keeping my original LiFePO4 battery). I‚Äôm including many, many spares and all the take-offs from the mid-drive conversion.  The 750W Bafang BBSHD is from Luna Cycles, with the smallest possible chain ring (42 t), and has been programmed for hot-rod performance (not race though. It‚Äôs still limited in speed so it‚Äôs legal, but wow is it strong.) This is the strongest motor I‚Äôve ridden; not even the 1000W units, fully unlimited, have the torque this one does. I have no idea why this is so; but it will put a grin on your face. I fitted a ¬Ω twist RH throttle for climbing really steep stuff; it will make it, no matter what you ask of it, and that was with the 36t rear 1st gear. Now that‚Äôs an even better 42t. It‚Äôs sure to please. It will also be better for pedaling without assist now that the gearing is better.  I have $2,750.00 invested in this. I‚Äôm asking  $1450.00  I can ship this bike to any US territory at the buyer's expense. Serious inquires only, please. If you‚Äôre reading this Ad, then I still have it for sale. This Ad will come down the moment it‚Äôs sold. First come, first served.    Reply to this listing, or call or text me at Two Zero Seven Three 5 0 ‚Äì Six 4 eight 4. Note: I‚Äôve been selling on CL for over 10 years; I know the game. If you email me, you must include your full name and phone # or I‚Äôll consider your email to be SPAM and delete it without a reply. If you ask if I still have it, again I‚Äôll consider your email to be spam. title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System for Motorcycles/bikes
text: Like new condition, had it less than a month. Just purchased a new bike that has a TPMS from the factory, so I no longer need this one.   Just download the FOBO app, sync it up, and you're ready to ride!   FOBO Bike 2 Tire Pressure Monitoring Systems  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) for every biker. FOBO Bike 2 uses the latest Bluetooth 5.0 technology that works directly with your smartphone that has Bluetooth smart Ready (Bluetooth 4.0 or above) capability in order to use FOBO Bike 2. Currently FOBO Bike 2 works best with iOS 9.3 and Android 5.0 or later.  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system for every biker  * View on demand tire pressure & temperature  * Monitors tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range  * Detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies  * Sends instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/smartwatch/Bluetooth headset  * Easy install on any motorcycle without running wires, drilling holes, and tedious programming   The main function of FOBO Bike 2 is to monitor tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range. It detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies. It then transmits the readings to a smart phone where the user can browse. The user can set upper and lower thresholds of the air pressure. FOBO Bike 2 can send instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/ smartwatch/ Bluetooth headset. It will monitor the pressure based on the thresholds with its smart algorithm and will provide three levels of alerts when the thresholds are breached

title: CrossCurrent S e-bike medium frame
text: Juiced Bikes brand, CrossCurrent S model The medium size frame (16.5‚Äù) it should fit people between the heights of 5‚Äô4‚Äù & 6‚Äô  This particular model is no longer being manufactured. The closest equivalent is the CrossCurrent X, which also has a rack for panniers and fenders. This bike had an upgrade of a frame with "brushed aluminum" finish, whereby only the frames with the highest quality welds and craftsmanship were selected, since the metal was given a clear finish.  It also has an upgraded 17.4 amp hour battery pack, which at 48 Volts can provide 835 Watt hours. Check out the photos and look for a chart showing your potential riding range based on your speed and this particular battery pack (Super Extended). I have primarily used the electric assist with a torque sensor, rather than cadence. This makes my peddling feel rather natural.  The harder you pedal, the more power it gives to the motor. If you pedal lighter, less power goes to the motor. It has different levels of electrical assist. The lowest level (Eco) is designed to just overcome the extra weight of the bike. Levels 1, 2 & 3 provide increasing assist up to 28 mph. Level S which stands for ‚ÄúSport‚Äù continues to provide assist without any upper speed limit.  The weight of the bike is significant. Maybe about 54 pounds or a little more since I have the extended range battery. You must take that into account when braking. The bike is designed to support the extra weight with extra heavy duty spokes, frame, and hydraulic brakes. I like the idea that the battery pack is on the front down tube and not on the back wheel. This means that one can haul some loads with the bike rack ‚Äî rated for 50 pounds. The total payload limit is 350 pounds.  I believe you will find the bike is very well thought out and designed and the craftsmanship is excellent. Customer support is pretty good as well. There was a little bit of assembly required when I received the bike. The headlamp/light they sent had some glue in one of the receptacles. The company quickly sent me a replacement. I also had a time or two when a fault signal appeared on the charging unit. Technical support readily resolved the issue by walking me through some simple steps.  I have an electronic copy of the instruction manual.  There are a few scratches on it when is the bike tipped over. All damage seems to be cosmetic. I had a slow leak in the rear tire and had a local bike shop replace the tube. It was a bit of a challenge for them to get the wheel off, but they managed.

title: CrossCurrent S e-bike medium frame
text: Juiced Bikes brand, CrossCurrent S model The medium size frame (16.5‚Äù) it should fit people between the heights of 5‚Äô4‚Äù & 6‚Äô  This particular model is no longer being manufactured. The closest equivalent is the CrossCurrent X, which also has a rack for panniers and fenders. This bike had an upgrade of a frame with "brushed aluminum" finish, whereby only the frames with the highest quality welds and craftsmanship were selected, since the metal was given a clear finish.  It also has an upgraded 17.4 amp hour battery pack, which at 48 Volts can provide 835 Watt hours. Check out the photos and look for a chart showing your potential riding range based on your speed and this particular battery pack (Super Extended). I have primarily used the electric assist with a torque sensor, rather than cadence. This makes my peddling feel rather natural.  The harder you pedal, the more power it gives to the motor. If you pedal lighter, less power goes to the motor. It has different levels of electrical assist. The lowest level (Eco) is designed to just overcome the extra weight of the bike. Levels 1, 2 & 3 provide increasing assist up to 28 mph. Level S which stands for ‚ÄúSport‚Äù continues to provide assist without any upper speed limit.  The weight of the bike is significant. Maybe about 54 pounds or a little more since I have the extended range battery. You must take that into account when braking. The bike is designed to support the extra weight with extra heavy duty spokes, frame, and hydraulic brakes. I like the idea that the battery pack is on the front down tube and not on the back wheel. This means that one can haul some loads with the bike rack ‚Äî rated for 50 pounds. The total payload limit is 350 pounds.  I believe you will find the bike is very well thought out and designed and the craftsmanship is excellent. Customer support is pretty good as well. There was a little bit of assembly required when I received the bike. The headlamp/light they sent had some glue in one of the receptacles. The company quickly sent me a replacement. I also had a time or two when a fault signal appeared on the charging unit. Technical support readily resolved the issue by walking me through some simple steps.  I have an electronic copy of the instruction manual.  There are a few scratches on it when is the bike tipped over. All damage seems to be cosmetic. I had a slow leak in the rear tire and had a local bike shop replace the tube. It was a bit of a challenge for them to get the wheel off, but they managed.

title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System for Motorcycles/bikes
text: Like new condition, had it less than a month. Just purchased a new bike that has a TPMS from the factory, so I no longer need this one.   Just download the FOBO app, sync it up, and you're ready to ride!   FOBO Bike 2 Tire Pressure Monitoring Systems  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) for every biker. FOBO Bike 2 uses the latest Bluetooth 5.0 technology that works directly with your smartphone that has Bluetooth smart Ready (Bluetooth 4.0 or above) capability in order to use FOBO Bike 2. Currently FOBO Bike 2 works best with iOS 9.3 and Android 5.0 or later.  FOBO Bike 2 is a SMART tire pressure monitoring system for every biker  * View on demand tire pressure & temperature  * Monitors tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range  * Detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies  * Sends instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/smartwatch/Bluetooth headset  * Easy install on any motorcycle without running wires, drilling holes, and tedious programming   The main function of FOBO Bike 2 is to monitor tire pressure in real time while riding or when in Bluetooth range. It detects slow or fast leak and alerts users to anomalies. It then transmits the readings to a smart phone where the user can browse. The user can set upper and lower thresholds of the air pressure. FOBO Bike 2 can send instant audio, haptic and text alerts on a smartphone/ smartwatch/ Bluetooth headset. It will monitor the pressure based on the thresholds with its smart algorithm and will provide three levels of alerts when the thresholds are breached

An invitation to see how good you can be, written in Milwaukee steel.InfotainmentWhen we go to work on the infotainment system for a Harley-Davidson Touring motorcycle we follow one simple principle. If you‚Äôre going to live in the saddle of a top-end touring bike, you deserve better sound than most people have in their living rooms. More sound. Purer sound. Big, full-color touch screens. Switches that are located where you intuitively want them to be and can reach without removing your hands from the grips. Voice activation for your music, phone and GPS. Think of it this way. Back in the day there was nothing wrong with the sound of Johnny crackling out of a dashboard Philco. But what the latest Project RUSHMORE infotainment systems do for your ears, and eyes, is infinitely better.StyleWith a name like Project RUSHMORE, you know we were aiming high when we set out to rethink what riders experience on our Touring machines. These weren‚Äôt just motorcycles. They‚Äôre part of the American landscape. So we set about perfecting the way they work, feel and look the only way we could. By riding. Millions of miles. Countless hours. More grueling road tests than any sane person would ever want to endure. We discovered the technology and the innovations to make the ride better. And through it all we never took our eyes of the style of the machine. Give your eyes a slow ride from fender tip to fender tip You see classic Harley-Davidson style and a sleek modern look come through at the same time. Clean. Tight. Modern. As up-to-date as the weather report blasting out the infotainment system. As timeless as the road is endless.A27FBAFAEA464DBBB650D168074EE06C 33277550 10374942

text: Like new. Price firm. Cash only. No trades.  Size Medium fits most riders.  Bought for my wife who rode twice.  Bike rack stored indoors.  Tuned by Lewis and Clark.  The fast-rolling 700c wheels and lightweight ALUXX aluminum frame gives this all-new bike confident, easy-to maneuver handling when you're zipping through crowded city streets. title: FELT 9 Trail Hardtail "29er" - BEAST OF A BIKE
text: We all get a little old...a little plump, and life changes. I'm preparing to move so instead of putting my beautiful Felt 9 Trail bike in storage I've decided to pass it on to someone else. I just don't ride anymore.  Specs:  2011 Felt 9 Trail (hard tail) Butted 6061-aluminum 19.5 inch frame SR SunTour 11 series adjustable front fork Shimano, 8-speed: 11-32 cassette  Shimano shifters Tektro IO mechanical disc brakes MTB XC Riser handle bars MTB platform pedals  Front tire/wheel: Bontrager FR3 EXP on 29" Alexrims Adventurer wheel (I added this myself to give more front bite in turns)  Rear tire/wheel: WTB Prowler SL 2.1 29" Felt wheel (stock)  Listing all that goodness makes me hate to let this go...but let's proceed.  With a 19.5 inch frame, this is a substantial bike but it handles brilliantly. Lightweight for it's size and being a 29" wheely the bike sings on the trail. This would be perfect for a larger rider (I'm 6'4") or for those who like to sit on top of the world when they ride.  It is in great, used condition. I actually didn't ride very much after I purchased the bike new. It has been hanging in my shop for the better part of the past decade.   There are some minimal scrapes and scratches that are to be expected but everything functions just like it did the day I road it from the shop. The only real damage is the sprocket guard which I only noticed was broken when washing the bike for sale. No idea how/when it happened. Of course, it does not at all interfere with riding and can be easily replaced (around $10-$15 at Wal-Mart). Slight wear on the seat/post as pictured.   Included is a like-new Schwinn aluminum gear rack, a brand new tube along with my Presta valve adapter which makes airing up the tires a breeze.  This is one of those "lifetime" bikes that will give you years of enjoyment on the trails.  Please ask any and all questions prior to purchase as the sale is final. If you would like additional pictures of a specific part of the bike I'll do my best to get them for you.  I've listed my bike in multiple places but if it sells I'll delete this listing. In other words, if you see this listing it's still available.

title: 1981 Suzuki DS125X
text: 1981 Suzuki DS125X  Great 2-stroke bike but pretty rare in the US, couldn't find very many others like it. Despite that, its a cool retro ride or a good starter.  Was restored to running condition recently and currently has a new carburetor, rebuilt clutch, new rear brake, rebuilt front forks, a new chain, and new bridgestone tires. Everything works as is should including the oil injection. No gas mixing needed!  Starts on the first kick with choke, even in cold weather, and can start with no choke in the summer. Kickstarter, no electric start. Great survivor original bike.  Have some spare parts for it, comes with spare carb, new clutch plates, the old clutch basket, old rear brake drum, and old chain. 1200 FIRM.

title: 2015 HD FLHTK Ultra Limited
text: Great bike and I've had a lot of fun on it, but I'm getting a little old for such a big bike and it deserves better than collecting dust in the garage.  One owner, meticulously maintained, always garaged, in very good condition.  Two-tone color: Mysterious Red/Cayenne.  True 49-State bike - I have ridden this bike to every state except Hawaii, and it still has plenty of get-up-and-go.  The only non-stock thing on the bike is the radio antennas - old whip antennas replaced with short ‚Äústubs‚Äù when they wore out.  Cruise control, heated handgrips, security system, touchscreen navigation, radio, CB, cargo rack.  Front tire good, rear tire nearly new.  Extras: sheepskin seat cushion, 3 helmets, rain gear, orange safety vest, intercom system, external bag for mounting on cargo rack, and more.  Similar bikes are listed for ~$20K on Autotrader, but the dealer will only pay me about half the Kelley Blue Book trade-in value.  I'd rather see someone else get a good deal than the dealer make a mint off the bike they assured me would hold its value.  Text, email, or leave a voicemail message. Three-213010116.

title: Think Grow LED Horticulture Grow lights! Commercial grade! New Cond.!
text: Hello Craigslist!!    I have for Sale some 'ThinkGrow' LED Model-W Grow lights. Fully dimmable and full spectrum. If you're looking at this ad, you should know that these are the Ferrari of grow lights. They are in AMAZING condition and work perfectly. No issues whatsoever.   ...keeping it short and sweet, They are 1000 Watt Equivalent using only 630 Real Watts. Commercial grade. Extremely efficient, FULL spectrum. Google them for yourself for full specs because its too much to get into here. All you need to know is these are the best of the best. Perfect for cannabis, indoor gardening, micro-green farming, growing your own fruits and veggies indoors. Any type of agriculture cultivation really.   They are able to be ran in configuration with one another or individually using a Trolmaster controller. You can run them without the controller and just plug them into a regular 120v outlet. Ill include the adapter for you. These are the cream of the crop of horticulture lights. Super easy to use.  THESE CAN BE RAN IN EITHER VEG OR FLOWER.  The light bars are removable.   VEG IT COVERS A 7X7 SQUARE FOOT GROW SPACE EACH LIGHT  FLOWER IT COVERS A 5X5 SQUARE FOOT GROW SPACE EACH LIGHT  They normally run $1300+ each IF you can find them. I'll do $1000 each. In the pictures they are at 1% power just to give you and idea, at 100% they are absolutely insane. At 100% power they are as powerful and bright as a 1000W has yet they only use 630 WATTS!  Everybody is worried about density with LED and it is absolutely there. These are full spectrum and more efficient then a HPS. Full spectrum = more purple and more flavor! LED is the future, look at all the big facilities transitioning to LED. Equivalent yields and quality and nearly half the electricity cost.   If you buy MORE then 2 I'll do $900 each. I have 6 left. May be interested in trades for quads? dirt bikes? No more equipment. I have other items if interested. AC units, c02 tanks etc. Flood tables, Everything you need.

title: 2016 KTM Duke 690
text: This bike is in excellent condition. Tires are good, it needs nothing, it's ready to ride. Includes rear stand, fly screen, tail tidy, stock mirrors, coax acc plug, and that odd skid plate. Handlebar is the comfortable KTM SMT unit, the stock (wide) bar is included. Currently running a 15T sprocket on the front, includes the stock 16T if you want the high stock gearing. I just changed the oil (Motorex) and ALL four filters. Registered till 4/2023.  This bike hasn't been molested, hooned, or tracked. Completely stock engine, emissions, and exhaust. Trakpac is not installed, you can get that for $300 at your fav KTM dealer if you intend to hoon or track the bike.  I'm the second owner, I bought it about one year ago. I'm an old guy and I ride and run my bikes pretty conservatively. The original owner is a reasonable fellow that mostly used it to daily commute Long Beach to Redondo Beach till he got scared one time too many out on the freeway.  It is a fun bike, and gets 50-55MPG. I'm not riding much and now I'm buying a vacation home that needs work and will suck up my free time.  Cash only. My price is firm, it's a hard to find model and I'm not in a hurry.  Thanks Randy  There are just so many time wasting scammers these days. We will have to talk by phone - I will not respond to a text message - call me or text me a number and I'll call you back.  Email is OK but I will not email direct, only through CL proxy - but you will have to call me anyway so just call.   If you want to run the VIN it's in the picture of the NICB report.  And finally, if the ad is up, it's for sale!    seven6zero - 3seven7 - 7three05
